Use the standard library
This is how to select_words of s and n:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that word is ""
   Remember that i is 0
   Remember that len is s's length
   Do this len times:
      Remember that c is item i in s
      When c is " ", then:
         When word's length is n, then:
            Add result to word
         End when
         Remember that word is ""
      But, if not:
         Add word to c
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   When word's length is n, then:
      Add result to word
   End when
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> select_words of "" and 1
[]
>>> select_words of "Mary had a little lamb" and 4
["little"]
>>> select_words of "Mary had a little lamb" and 3
["had"]